Gawin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usistily.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sistily</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/28/02 9:20:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3837.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fungi tunic of luclin?</span><hr size=1> I have done this quest about 15 times. We have done all 3 sizes beers and tried all 3 callers. Some things I've noticed. the easiest is the bottle size beer = 3 minutes spawn rate, Jug of beer = 2 minutes 30 second spawn rate and the keg of beer = 2 minute spawn rate. All 3 sizes of beer will spawn the same, ie. 3 mobs will spawn down into the cave and 2 mobs will spawn out infront of the cave. I have done this quest with as many as 15 people and as low as 5 people. <br>
<br>
The quest doesn't seem to stop unless you choose to stop it. The caller will summon beasts for you all day if you choose. You can end the quest by handing in the item (book) he gives you in return for the beer at the start of the quest.<br>
<br>
Named mobs can spawn in the front of the cave and in the back of the cave. Named can also drop a nice 32 AC, 15 STA, 10 WIS, 15 DR shield, good for clerics and druids. Also drops some average 1 HB, 2HB weapon, but with nice graphics. Exp seemed to be fairly good.<br>
<br>
One word of warning, if another group(s) is doing the quest in one of the other 2 caves, don't go wandering around outside your own quest cave. You can argo the other caves outside spawns and soon have too many beasties to handle. If you are killing the mobs as he summons them, you should never have more than 5 beasties up at a time.<br>
<br>
Sistily<br>
Gnome Warlord<br>
